UOWN | Origination | Allow adding non-standard email domains
Aberto
  Tíquete criado 2 dias atrás por Yuri Araujo
Synopsis
On the Merchant page, users can add email addresses to multiple fields, including fields that are enabled only when a specific toggle is turned on. Currently, when attempting to add an email with a non-standard domain (e.g. sample@bds.services), the UI does not allow the email to be added.

It was observed that emails with this domain already exist in the system, likely added directly via database, indicating that the Front End validation is preventing these domains from being added through the UI.

The system must allow these types of valid domains to be added directly via the UI to avoid future issues and manual database interventions.

Feature Request | Business Requirements



        
      Adjust Front End email validation to accept valid non-standard domains

        
      Allow these emails to be added in:


        
      Standard Merchant email fields

        
      Fields enabled by the Send Automated Funding Report toggle



        
      Do not change behavior of already stored emails

        
      Avoid the need for direct database updates for new entries

        
      The system should allow adding emails with valid domains, even if they are not commonly used

        
      Emails like sample@bds.services should be accepted normally via the UI

![alt text](image.png)

Steps-to-Reproduce



        
      Go to Origination


        
      Navigate to the Merchants page

        
      Open the edit page for any Merchant

        
      In the middle column, locate the Send Automated Funding Report toggle

        
      Turn the toggle ON

        
      Observe that two new email fields appear

        
      In the Funding Report Emails field, try adding sample@bds.services

Testing Steps
Confirm that now, after reproducing the case:

Go to Origination

Navigate to the Merchants page
Open the edit page for any Merchant
In the middle column, locate the Send Automated Funding Report toggle
Turn the toggle ON
Observe that two new email fields appear
In the Funding Report Emails field, try adding sample@bds.services


The email is added successfully.

